using broker-dealer accounts that passed rebates back to their customers to
place initial orders on one side of the market, and then using
broker-dealer accounts that did not charge fees for taking liquidity for
his subsequent orders on the other side of the market. When identifying a
product to trade, Gu and his friend and business associate, Yong Lee,
